Parsons Boulevard, at the N.E. corner of 72nd Avenue, showing two homes, the one on the right being of 18th century construction and the one on the left being of recent times. The old house was the G. Van Dine (Van Dyke) property in 1873 and 1891 and was just north of Quarrelsome Lane, where the old Jamaica Road bent westward around the Campbell and
Elflein farms.
P. L. Sperr  March 23, 1927
